I"(<p><img src="/assets/img/linux/icons-linux.jpg" alt="The 8 Best Icon Themes for Your Linux" /></p>

<p>I made this list based on my experiences with icon themes, some of them have already been laid out in some <a href="https://www.youtube.com/TerminalRootTV">Terminal Root Channel</a> videos, but others have been combed and tested to be part of here.</p>

<p>Installation is standard on any Linux, ie just download the package, extract and move to the icon directory in your user’s root folder: <code class="highlighter-rouge">~/.icons/</code>, if there is no such directory, create: <code class="highlighter-rouge">mkdir ~/.icons</code> . Whether to enable will depend on each Interface/Desktop Environment and window managers.</p>

<p>Let’s get to know these 8 best!</p>

