<h2 id="01-deepin">01. <a href="https://www.gnome-look.org/p/1191167/">Deepin</a></h2>

<p><img src="/assets/img/linux/deepin.jpg" alt="Deepin" /></p>

<p>Deepin I think was one of the icon themes that I used most to date, does not harm the view and even customizes some directories facilitating the quick view. It has an app icon theme that recognizes most and doesn’t distort which doesn’t make it hard to identify. Worth trying:</p>

<div class="text-center">
  <p><a style="cursor:pointer;" href="http://bit.ly/DeepinIconTR">
   <button style="cursor:pointer;" class="btn-lg btn-primary">
   <i class="fas fa-download"></i> Download Deepin icons
   </button>
  </a></p>
</div>

<p>To install unzip after download and move to the icon directory, to work, just activate in the configuration menu of your desktop.</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nb">tar </span>zxvf Deepin.tar.gz
<span class="nb">mv </span>Deepin/ ~/.icons/</code></pre></figure>

