<h2 id="08-cupertino">08. <a href="https://www.gnome-look.org/p/1102582/">Cupertino</a></h2>

<p><img src="/assets/img/linux/cupertino.jpg" alt="Cupertino Circle" /></p>

<p>And finally, the Cupertino, he is very similar to Mojave, but has some modified tones. I put in this list precisely for the same reason as the previous one, the number of people who like it is large, and of course, I found it very cool too.</p>

<p>To install unzip after download and move to the icon directory. To work simply activate in the configuration menu of your desktop.</p>

<div class="text-center">
  <p><a style="cursor:pointer;" href="http://bit.ly/CupertinoIconTR1">
